Uses .sum() to add them up
Divides by n - 1









Use .powi(2) to square values.
Use your previously defined mean() function inside variance().






View hint

fn variance(x: &[f64]) -&gt; f64 {
    let n = x.len() as f64;
    let avg = mean(x);
    let sq_diffs: f64 = x
        .iter()
        .map(|xi| ___ )  // squared difference here
